[
    {
        "text": "[Music]",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "there is",
        "start": 3.439,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "nothing more important in physics than",
        "start": 4.0,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "the speed of light its abbreviation",
        "start": 6.399,
        "duration": 4.721
    },
    {
        "text": "c literally means constant like the",
        "start": 8.4,
        "duration": 3.359
    },
    {
        "text": "constant",
        "start": 11.12,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "the one that matters but here's a secret",
        "start": 11.759,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "the speed of light changes all the time",
        "start": 13.84,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "it's about 25 slower in water 35",
        "start": 15.839,
        "duration": 5.121
    },
    {
        "text": "in glass and more than twice as slow",
        "start": 18.96,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "when traveling through a diamond",
        "start": 20.96,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "sea itself measures the speed of light",
        "start": 22.32,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "in a vacuum about 300 million meters per",
        "start": 24.16,
        "duration": 2.959
    },
    {
        "text": "second",
        "start": 26.64,
        "duration": 2.559
    },
    {
        "text": "and it's literally the fastest anything",
        "start": 27.119,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "in the universe can go and you know what",
        "start": 29.199,
        "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
        "text": "in nature light is always fast because",
        "start": 31.199,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "25",
        "start": 33.84,
        "duration": 2.239
    },
    {
        "text": "slower than the fastest thing in the",
        "start": 34.559,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "universe is still stupid fast but in the",
        "start": 36.079,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "lab",
        "start": 38.559,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "scientists have done something",
        "start": 39.28,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "extraordinary created beams of light",
        "start": 40.559,
        "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
        "text": "that are slower than a car and then with",
        "start": 43.2,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "the literal flick of a switch",
        "start": 46.239,
        "duration": 3.361
    },
    {
        "text": "they can freeze that beam in place if",
        "start": 47.68,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "you're thinking that sounds tricky",
        "start": 49.6,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "you're right but if scientists can",
        "start": 51.52,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "master it this could be the key to our",
        "start": 53.039,
        "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
        "text": "computing future the key to catching a",
        "start": 54.719,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "beam of light is called",
        "start": 56.48,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "electromagnetically induced transparency",
        "start": 57.879,
        "duration": 4.441
    },
    {
        "text": "and it was first observed in 1991 it's a",
        "start": 60.239,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "way of taking something opaque",
        "start": 62.32,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "and making it perfectly transparent at a",
        "start": 64.08,
        "duration": 3.359
    },
    {
        "text": "given wavelength",
        "start": 66.24,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "using nothing but a couple beams of",
        "start": 67.439,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "light which weirdly enough is possible",
        "start": 69.119,
        "duration": 4.801
    },
    {
        "text": "to do it you need an opaque cloud of gas",
        "start": 71.2,
        "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
        "text": "say sodium gas that's super cold so",
        "start": 73.92,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "atoms aren't moving very much that cloud",
        "start": 76.88,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "also needs to be in a vacuum so there's",
        "start": 78.72,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "no outside interference",
        "start": 80.479,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "and the atoms in the cloud need to have",
        "start": 81.84,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "electrons with three available energy",
        "start": 83.6,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "levels initially the electrons in each",
        "start": 85.84,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "atom are in the lowest energy level then",
        "start": 87.6,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "you shine a pair of lasers into the gas",
        "start": 89.52,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "the first is called the probe and it",
        "start": 91.439,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "emits light with just the right amount",
        "start": 93.52,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "of energy to take electrons from the",
        "start": 95.28,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "first energy level",
        "start": 97.04,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "to the third if you were to shine it",
        "start": 98.159,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "into the cloud by itself it would all",
        "start": 99.68,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "get instantly absorbed by the electrons",
        "start": 101.439,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "jumping up to that third energy level",
        "start": 103.52,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "so the cloud would stay opaque because",
        "start": 105.28,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "being opaque just means you don't let",
        "start": 107.119,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "light through now there's another laser",
        "start": 108.72,
        "duration": 2.719
    },
    {
        "text": "called the coupling beam",
        "start": 110.159,
        "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
        "text": "and it has the right amount of energy to",
        "start": 111.439,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "take electrons from the second energy",
        "start": 113.2,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "level to the third except",
        "start": 114.799,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "if all the electrons are in the lowest",
        "start": 116.24,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "energy level there aren't any to move",
        "start": 117.92,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "from level two to three so the beam just",
        "start": 119.68,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "passes through untouched so if you shine",
        "start": 121.439,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "the light separately",
        "start": 123.439,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "only the coupling beam goes through the",
        "start": 124.479,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "cloud but when you shine the two beams",
        "start": 126.079,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "together",
        "start": 127.6,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "things get weird if you turn the",
        "start": 128.56,
        "duration": 3.039
    },
    {
        "text": "coupling beam on first",
        "start": 130.0,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "and then the probe beam the probe can",
        "start": 131.599,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "suddenly shine straight through",
        "start": 133.68,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "what happens is the coupling beam is",
        "start": 135.12,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "trying to shift the electrons from level",
        "start": 137.04,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "two to three",
        "start": 138.959,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "but at the same time the probe beam is",
        "start": 139.84,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "trying to shift them from one to three",
        "start": 142.08,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "faced with these two tugs the electron",
        "start": 143.84,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "basically gets trapped between them",
        "start": 146.16,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "effectively ending up in level one and",
        "start": 148.16,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "level two at the same time and when that",
        "start": 150.319,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "happens the electron doesn't absorb",
        "start": 152.959,
        "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
        "text": "photons from either",
        "start": 154.72,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "beam of light physicists call this",
        "start": 156.0,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "situation a dark state which",
        "start": 157.76,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "sounds ominous but it just means that",
        "start": 159.84,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "the electron ends up in the dark about",
        "start": 161.519,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "the presence of either laser now that",
        "start": 163.519,
        "duration": 3.281
    },
    {
        "text": "the light's not getting absorbed the",
        "start": 165.12,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "cloud becomes transparent to the laser",
        "start": 166.8,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "and the probe beam can travel straight",
        "start": 169.04,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "through it's a neat trick but it doesn't",
        "start": 170.8,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "come for free the probe can",
        "start": 172.48,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "pass through but it does so super slowly",
        "start": 174.16,
        "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
        "text": "see the probe beam is made up of a bunch",
        "start": 177.36,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "of light waves at frequencies that are",
        "start": 179.36,
        "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
        "text": "really similar but not quite the same as",
        "start": 181.2,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "they enter the cloud",
        "start": 183.92,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "those waves slow down at different rates",
        "start": 185.28,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and start to interfere with each other",
        "start": 187.68,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "and that causes the entire probe beam to",
        "start": 189.44,
        "duration": 2.719
    },
    {
        "text": "slow down",
        "start": 191.519,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "like instead of traveling at a billion",
        "start": 192.159,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "kilometers an hour it's suddenly going",
        "start": 193.92,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "more like",
        "start": 195.92,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "25 slow enough that you could keep up",
        "start": 196.64,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "with this beam of light",
        "start": 198.72,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "on a bike that sudden slow down also",
        "start": 200.0,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "bunches up the light beam into a tiny",
        "start": 202.0,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "sluggish package but physicists weren't",
        "start": 203.92,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "done once they'd slowed light to a crawl",
        "start": 205.92,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "in some cases they went on to stop light",
        "start": 208.4,
        "duration": 4.399
    },
    {
        "text": "altogether they accomplished that by",
        "start": 211.04,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "turning",
        "start": 212.799,
        "duration": 2.561
    },
    {
        "text": "off the coupling beam while that",
        "start": 213.28,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "scrunched up package of light was making",
        "start": 215.36,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "its way through the gas",
        "start": 217.2,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "at that point the package completely",
        "start": 218.4,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "vanished once again the energy in that",
        "start": 219.92,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "light got absorbed into the sodium atoms",
        "start": 221.76,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "but what's incredible",
        "start": 223.84,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "is that that light wasn't just gone when",
        "start": 225.12,
        "duration": 4.399
    },
    {
        "text": "they turned the coupling beam back on",
        "start": 227.28,
        "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
        "text": "a package of light emerged with the same",
        "start": 229.519,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "exact phase and energy",
        "start": 231.84,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "as it had before somehow the sodium",
        "start": 233.599,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "atoms were",
        "start": 236.0,
        "duration": 2.959
    },
    {
        "text": "storing information about that beam of",
        "start": 236.799,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "light so far",
        "start": 238.959,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "scientists have been able to freeze",
        "start": 240.159,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "light for up to 1.5 seconds but it's not",
        "start": 241.519,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "just for kicks this might also have",
        "start": 243.68,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "applications in fields like",
        "start": 245.36,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "quantum computing and cryptography for",
        "start": 246.64,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "instance the last time you bought a",
        "start": 248.799,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "computer",
        "start": 250.159,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "one of the specs you probably had to",
        "start": 250.799,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "pick was the amount of memory or ram",
        "start": 252.239,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "that you wanted the ability to store",
        "start": 254.0,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "something for later is kind of a",
        "start": 255.519,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "fundamental part of what makes computers",
        "start": 256.799,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "useful but the quantum computers built",
        "start": 258.4,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "so far don't really have memory since",
        "start": 259.919,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "quantum information is more complex than",
        "start": 261.68,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "ones and zeros",
        "start": 263.44,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "these machines can't store information",
        "start": 264.479,
        "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
        "text": "like a regular computer does",
        "start": 266.16,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "electromagnetically induced transparency",
        "start": 267.52,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "seems to offer one way to solve that",
        "start": 269.84,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "problem after all stopping light is all",
        "start": 271.52,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "about getting atoms to hold on to",
        "start": 273.52,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "information in the configuration of",
        "start": 275.199,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "their electrons and that's exactly the",
        "start": 276.639,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "stuff quantum computers are working with",
        "start": 278.4,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "now having a lab's worth of equipment",
        "start": 280.32,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "keeping a bunch of sodium atoms near",
        "start": 282.0,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "absolute zero doesn't sound scalable",
        "start": 283.52,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "but there are other ways to induce",
        "start": 285.759,
        "duration": 3.281
    },
    {
        "text": "transparency some researchers have done",
        "start": 287.36,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "it using materials much closer to room",
        "start": 289.04,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "temperature",
        "start": 290.8,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "and in 2005 ibm developed a computer",
        "start": 291.36,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "chip",
        "start": 294.0,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "that could slow light by a factor of",
        "start": 294.4,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "300. that's a far cry from the 30",
        "start": 296.08,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "million time slowdown done using",
        "start": 298.4,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "ultracold atoms",
        "start": 300.32,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "and it's not the same as stopping light",
        "start": 301.6,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "but it's a step",
        "start": 304.16,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "and even if it's all a long way from",
        "start": 305.039,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "being useful there's definitely still",
        "start": 307.039,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "something incredible",
        "start": 309.199,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "about taking one of physics's most",
        "start": 310.16,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "important rules",
        "start": 312.08,
        "duration": 2.959
    },
    {
        "text": "and bending it to our will thanks for",
        "start": 313.44,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "watching this episode of scishow and a",
        "start": 315.039,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "special thanks to our patrons on patreon",
        "start": 316.72,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "who make it possible for us to make",
        "start": 318.639,
        "duration": 2.961
    },
    {
        "text": "videos like this if you want to join the",
        "start": 320.16,
        "duration": 3.039
    },
    {
        "text": "amazing community that keeps scishow",
        "start": 321.6,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "going",
        "start": 323.199,
        "duration": 3.911
    },
    {
        "text": "you can find out more at patreon.com",
        "start": 323.68,
